features: 2.1-Qt Capacity: This small air fryer is perfect for single serving items like sides, snacks, wings, and more.
Compact and Portable: Weighing in at less than 5 pounds, this mini air fryer is designed to be easily stored and carried with its sleek, compact design.
4 Cooking Functions: Choose from Air Fry, Roast, Bake, or Reheat, you can easily customize your cooking for your favorite foods.

The Quietest Operation: This airfryer cooks with noise levels less than 48dB, which is quieter than any other COSORI model. You can now cook your favorite foods without the distraction of annoying or disruptive noise.
Fast & Convenient: Even with no preheating needed, this air fryer cooks frozen food to crispy perfection in a matter of minutes at temperatures ranging from 170–400°F.
Up to 97% Less Oil: Enjoy crispy textures with up to 97% less oil than traditional frying.
Included Recipes: Enjoy 30 original recipes created by our chefs for your air fryer on the free VeSync app.
Dishwasher-Safe: Nonstick, BPA-Free accessories are easy to clean in the dishwasher.
A Great Gift: Give the foodies in your life the perfect-sized air fryer for fresh and crispy snacks.

Notification: This Air Fryer is ETL-Listed with a power rating of 120V / 900W, a temperature range of 170F°–400°F, and a 1-60 minute timer. Please note that this voltage only applies to the US and Canada.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Performance and design are both very good.
reviews.reviewText: Not only is this air fryer space saving and low noise, it cooks very well. The 'rectangular' basket is a real plus, much more versatile than a round basket. The digital controls are straightforward and the fryer pauses when the basket is pulled for 'shaking'. I like that it fits under the cabinet. It looks good enough to have on the counter, but I prefer to keep small appliances that I don't use every day under the counter. Less clutter.This fryer cooks very well with both frozen and fresh food. The cooking reference guide gets you in the ballpark right away for food, temp and time. Foods are flavorful, crispy on the outside and stay moist and juicy inside.The fryer cleans easily. It looks like it is designed to where the basket and grate are about the only parts that need washing, the inside of the fryer stays very clean even when using oil to cook (or cooking drumsticks!). Great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small size but great results
reviews.reviewText: I dont know how I loved without this before. As someone that was Mr. Microwave I now rarely even use the microwave unless I cant fit it in this air fryer.For the price it’s unbelievable has 4 pre programmed settings which honestly is all I ever use. I may adjust the time for the different modes but the temperature settings are perfect.This is also the perfect size for any of the small mini frozen pizzas even the deep dish kind and cooks them perfectly every-time.Super easy to clean comes with a nice little crisper tray. This thing also is absolutely perfect for reheating anything back to perfection especially any fast food reheats it including the buns perfect.If you were curious about getting into air frying like I was this is the perfect starter because of how easy it is to use, its super small foot print, preprogrammed settings and this brand is absolutely top notch also , buy it you wont regret it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for One!
reviews.reviewText: Wow! So easy to use. I had been having to heat an entire over to bake food, or use a skillet to cook my steak and other food and then have a big mess to clean up. This adorable air fryer is perfect for one and makes my meat delicious so fast! reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice, but do make sure you realize what size it really is.
reviews.reviewText: I'll be the first to say I'm really "duh" when it comes to seeing what real sizes are in my head. I thought the 2 quart would be fine for me as I cook alone a lot, but, it's pretty small. Not their fault - mine for misjudging what I needed. This is just large enough to fit ONE large burger "or" ONE large Chicken breast OR around 8 Mozzarella sticks, etc. You're not going to really get two different items of a decent portion size in this. One main item or some fries or sticks, etc. That's it. Knowing what I know now, I would have opted for one of their larger (4 qt?) models. That being said - it's easy to use, works well, and is pretty easy to clean. I do tend to have to leave the heat on a minute or two longer than instructions say (for my taste), but this is still a good way to eat healthier.
